03/04/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey is due for the second time to take over the Kabul Regional Command from France on Saturday (April 7th), local media reported on Tuesday.
Brigadier General Kasim Erdem will be assigned to lead the Regional Command, and the number of Turkish troops in the Afghan capital will jump from 750 to 1,150, mostly to provide logistical support and intelligence during the eight-month mandate.
The Kabul Regional Command, established in August 2006, is also assuming command of the International Security Assistance Force, which assists the Afghan government in security and restructuring.
(Sabah, Zaman, The New Anatolian, Turkishpress.com - 03/04/07)
